  "text": "The C. jejuni F38011 (clinical isolate), human10 (clinical isolate) [CITATION_1] , and ATCC 33560 (bovine feces isolate) strains were routinely cultivated either on Campylobacter agar (OXOID, Nepean, ON, Canada) plates supplemented with 5% defibrinated sheep blood (Alere Inc., Stittsville, ON, Canada) for 48 h or in Mueller-Hinton (MH) broth with constant shaking for 18 h at 37 • C in a microaerobic environment (i.e., 10% CO 2 ). Overnight C. jejuni cultures were individually prepared to 1 × 10 9 CFU/mL by adjusting OD 600 value. Then, a cocktail culture was prepared by combining equal volumes of each of the three cultures for further antimicrobial testing.",
